<h1 id="Pytwist-ExploringtheAPIusingtwister" style="margin: 30px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 24px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.25; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none;">Exploring the API using twister</h1><p style="margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: normal;">You can connect to the twister with a standard web browser using the address&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace;">https://&lt;core IP or hostname&gt;/twister</code>. When you first connect, you should see the basic twister interface with packages in the top-left frame, classes for a package in the bottom-left frame, and detailed information in the large right-side frame</p><div><br></div>